Text.Value: First, to the undercity. We must slay Voss, he who was once Jhe'stil Kith'rak.
First, to Sharess' Caress. We must slay Voss, he who was once Jhe'stil Kith'rak.
Yes - the Hammer is ours!
Yes - the Hammer is ours!
This is our chance to find out how much this devil bleeds.
To Sharess' Caress - Voss is still waiting. He must know of our victory.
Voss, he who was once Jhe'stil Kith'rak, is dead. And his so-called prince is soon to follow, once we free him from his astral prison.
For now, keep focused. Raphael will come to take back his treasure.

Text.Value: When we next enter the Astral Prism, the Prince of the Comet will soar again.
The means to Orpheus' release is in our hands.
You know what to do. When we next enter the Astral Prism, we will break Orpheus free.
When we next enter the Astral Prism, we will break Orpheus free.

To think, the traitor prince's release is within our grasp.
When we next enter the Astral Prism, we will slay he who would take Vlaakith's throne.
The traitor Prince Orpheus will follow, once we free him from his astral prison.
For a thousand years, he waited. For a thousand years, he remained faithful to Gith and her royal spawn.
The means to Orpheus' release is in our hands.
To think, Orpheus' release is within our grasp.

Synopsis: Laezel reaffirms her mission regarding the hammer and orpheus
